DOM inconsistencies aside, a big advantage jQuery has over native API is that it is just as easy to work with multiple elements as it is single elements.<p>Modifying your example:<p><pre><code>    var d = document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;div&#x27;);
    d = Array.prototype.slice.call(d);
    d.forEach(function(el){ el.classList.add(&#x27;new&#x27;) });
</code></pre>
Vesus:<p><pre><code>    $(&#x27;div&#x27;).addClass(&#x27;new&#x27;);</code></pre>
